'''Diop Tehuti Djed-Hotep Spence''' (born 9 August 2000) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]] for {{English football updater|TottenhH}} club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] and the [[England national football team|England national team]].

==Early life==
Spence is the younger brother of actress [[Karla-Simone Spence]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B6i9zhGF1bV/c/17870556268557011/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/iarchive/instagram/karlasimonespence_/2207598588431128277 |archive-date=25 December 2021 |url-access=registration|title=Proud Big sister🦁❤️ The future is bright! SPENCE WOI YOii!!! #winninggoal #borofc|author=Karla-Simone Spence|via=Instagram|date=26 December 2019|accessdate=30 November 2021}}{{cbignore}}</ref> He was born in England to a Jamaican father and Kenyan mother.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sports |first=Pulse |date=2025-03-14 |title=How Djed Spence's Kenyan mum Aisha helped revitalise his career in Italy |url=https://www.pulsesports.co.ke/football/story/how-djed-spences-kenyan-mum-aisha-helped-revitalise-his-career-in-italy-2025031402431459353 |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=Pulse Sports Kenya |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-02-18 |title=Everything We Know About Djed Spence's Wholesome Mum |url=https://www.thickaccent.com/2025/02/18/everything-we-know-about-djed-spences-wholesome-mum/ |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=Thick Accent |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title= Djed Spence hopes becoming first Muslim England player will inspire others| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cn95ldwqwygo|publisher=[[BBC|British Broadcasting Corporation]]|date=3 September 2025|access-date=4 September 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Middlesbrough===
Spence signed for [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] on 1 July 2018, having previously been with [[Fulham F.C. Academy|Fulham's academy]].<ref name="Middlesbrough"/><ref name="11v11">{{cite web | url=https://www.11v11.com/players/djed-spence-256770/ | title=11v11 | accessdate=15 August 2018 | website=11v11.com}}</ref> He made his debut for Middlesbrough in the [[EFL Cup]] on 14 August 2018, appearing as a substitute versus [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]] at the [[Riverside Stadium]].<ref name="Debut">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45092544|title=Middlesbrough 3–3 Notts County|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=15 August 2018|website=bbc.co.uk}}</ref> Spence made his league debut for Middlesbrough in a 1–0 win over Charlton Athletic on 7 December 2019, scoring his first league goal in a 1–0 win against Huddersfield Town on 26 December 2019.

On 11 January 2020, Spence won the EFL Young Player of the Month following his league debut, first goal, and three clean sheets.<ref name="Dec19 YPOTM">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51067940|title=Djed Spence: Middlesbrough defender wins December's EFL Young Player of the Month award|date=2020-01-11|access-date=2020-01-11|language=en-GB}}</ref>

====Nottingham Forest (loan)====
On 1 September 2021, it was announced Spence would join [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] on loan for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2021/september/Djed-Spence-signs-on-loan/|title=Djed Spence signs on loan|first=Nottingham Forest Football|last=Club|website=Nottingham Forest Football Club|date=September 2021 }}</ref> He scored his first goal for Forest in a 3–0 win over [[Birmingham City]] on 2 October.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58687612|title=Birmingham 0–3 Nottingham Forest|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=2 October 2021|access-date=26 January 2022}}</ref> Spence impressed in [[FA Cup]] victories over [[Premier League]] clubs [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], scoring the fourth in a 4–1 victory over the latter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60266470|title=Nottingham Forest 4–1 Leicester City: Forest defeat FA Cup holders Leicester|publisher=BBC Sport|date=6 February 2022|accessdate=20 March 2022}}</ref>

Spence was awarded the [[EFL Championship Player of the Month]] award for March 2022<ref name="Mar22 POTM">{{cite web|url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2022/april/08/spence-named-efl-player-of-the-month/|title=Spence named Sky Bet Championship Player of the Month|website=www.nottinghamforest.co.uk|date=8 April 2022}}</ref> as well as being nominated for the Goal of the Month award following his long range strike against [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2022/april/08/spence-nominated-for-sky-bet-goal-of-the-month/|title=Spence nominated for Sky Bet Championship Goal of the Month|website=www.nottinghamforest.co.uk|date=8 April 2022}}</ref> which he was ultimately awarded.<ref name="Mar22 GOTM">{{cite web|url=https://www.efl.com/news/2022/april/goal-of-the-month-march-winners/|title=Goal of the Month: March winners|website=www.efl.com|date=15 April 2022|accessdate=19 April 2022}}</ref> Having also been nominated for the Championship Young Player of the Season, Spence made it a hat-trick of awards for March 2022 when he won the EFL Young Player of the Month award for the second time in his career, becoming the first player to win it twice in the process.<ref name="Mar22 YPOTM">{{cite web|url=https://www.efl.com/news/2022/april/djed-spence-scoops-young-player-of-the-month-award/|title=Djed Spence scoops Young Player of the Month award|website=www.efl.com|date=20 April 2022|accessdate=22 April 2022}}</ref>

Spence played a vital role in [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]]'s promotion winning side, and was featured in both the EFL Championship Team of the Season and the PFA Championship team of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Football Manager EFL Team of the Season line-ups announced|url=https://www.efl.com/news/2022/april/football-manager-efl-team-of-the-season-line-ups-announced/ |access-date=2022-06-15|website=www.efl.com|language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=PFA Championship Team of the Year|url=https://www.thepfa.com/news/2022/6/9/pfa-awards-22-championship-toty |access-date=2022-06-15|website=www.thepfa.com|language=en}}</ref>

===Tottenham Hotspur===

On 19 July 2022, [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] announced the signing of Spence on a five-year contract, for a reported fee of £20 million.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Spence signs from Middlesbrough|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2022/july/spence-signs-from-middlesbrough/|date=19 July 2022|access-date=19 July 2022|website=Tottenham Hotspur|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|author=David Hytner|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/jul/19/tottenham-sign-djed-spence-from-middlesbrough-in-20m-deal|title=Tottenham seal Djed Spence signing from Middlesbrough in £20m deal|date=19 July 2022|website=www.theguardian.com|language=en}}</ref> Manager [[Antonio Conte]] swiftly disowned the signing, describing Spence as "an investment by the club." Spence later revealed that this "shattered [his] confidence."<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-07-20 |title=Spurs: Spence not my signing – Conte |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/cyjmddrr0w7o |access-date=2025-08-28 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Kilpatrick |first=Dan |date=2025-03-24 |title=Spurs star slams Conte as he reveals ex-boss 'shattered my confidence' |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/djed-spence-antonio-conte-tottenham-transfer-b1218539.html |access-date=2025-08-28 |website=The Standard |language=en}}</ref>

Ahead of Tottenham's game against Nottingham Forest on 29 August, Conte praised Spence for his efforts in training; he rewarded him with his Tottenham and [[2022–23 Premier League|Premier League]] debut, bringing him on as a late substitute in a 2–0 win.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Antonio Conte impressed with Djed Spence's desire to improve |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/antonio-conte-djed-spence-middlesbrough-spurs-premier-league-b2153956.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250814053042/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/antonio-conte-djed-spence-middlesbrough-spurs-premier-league-b2153956.html |archive-date=2025-08-14 |access-date=2025-08-28 |work=The Independent |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Nottingham Forest 0–2 Tottenham: Harry Kane scores 200th and 201st career league goals in hard-fought win |url=https://uk-sport-web.prod.oceanusorigin.com/football/news/11661/12681422/nottingham-forest-0-2-tottenham-harry-kane-scores-200th-and-201st-career-league-goals-in-hard-fought-win |access-date=2022-09-01 |website=Sky Sports |language=en }}{{Dead link|date=February 2024 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Further appearances were limited, however: Spence had made just six by the end of January.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Stade Rennais loan for Spence |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2023/january/stade-rennais-loan-for-spence/ |access-date=2025-08-28 |website=Tottenham Hotspur |language=en}}</ref>

====Loan to Rennes====
On 31 January 2023, Spence joined French [[Ligue 1]] side [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Stade Rennais]] on a loan until the end of the [[2022–23 Stade Rennais F.C. season|2022–23 season]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Djed Spence, nouveau Latéral droit Rennais!|url=https://www.staderennais.com/djed-spence-nouveau-lateral-droit-rennais|date=31 January 2023|access-date=31 January 2023|website=Stade Rennais F.C.|language=fr}}</ref> He made ten appearances for Rennes, including nine starts,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.staderennais.com/en/first-team/djed-spence|title=Djed Spence – First Team Profile|access-date=6 October 2024|website=Stade Rennais}}</ref> one of which was a 2–0 win over [[Paris Saint-Germain]] at the [[Parc des Princes]], the Parisian team's first league defeat at home in 23 months.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65009740|title=Paris St-Germain 0–2 Rennes: Hosts suffer first home league defeat since April 2021|date=23 March 2024|access-date=6 October 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

Spence's minutes became limited after Rennes captain [[Hamari Traoré|Hamari Traore]] returned from injury in April, and the loan was cut short by a knee injury which saw Spence return to England for treatment.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Guest |first=Rob |date=2023-05-12 |title=Djed Spence returns to Tottenham after Rennes boss confirms injury blow |url=https://www.football.london/tottenham-hotspur-fc/players/djed-spence-tottenham-injury-rennes-26901588 |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=Football London |language=en}}</ref>

====Loan to Leeds United====
On 30 August 2023, [[EFL Championship]] club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] announced the signing of Spence on a season-long loan from Tottenham Hotspur.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-30 |title=Leeds United sign Djed Spence on loan from Tottenham Hotspur |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/en/news/leeds-united-sign-djed-spence-on-loan-from-tottenham-hotspur |access-date= |publisher=Leeds United F.C. |language=en}}</ref> He made his debut for the club in a [[2023–24 EFL Championship|Championship]] fixture against [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]] on 2 September, coming on as a second-half substitute in a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66624469|title=Leeds United 0–0 Sheffield Wednesday: Owls frustrate Leeds to win first point|date=3 September 2024|access-date=6 October 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

On 18 September 2023, Spence suffered a knee ligament injury in training that would see him out of action for until December.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-27 |title=Djed Spence Injury Update |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/en/news/djed-spence-injury-update |access-date= |publisher=Leeds United F.C. |language=en}}</ref><ref name='genoa'>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5189767/2024/01/13/djed-spence-leeds-spurs-genoa/|title=Djed Spence: Sent back to Spurs by Leeds – can he finally find his feet at Genoa?|date=13 January 2024|access-date=6 October 2024|website=The Athletic}}</ref> He made his comeback from injury on 9 December, playing 20 minutes against [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]]<ref name='genoa'/> and went on to start Leeds' next five [[2023–24 EFL Championship|Championship]] fixtures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/leeds-united-transfer-latest-whites-exercise-recall-option-to-allow-djed-spence-to-return-to-premier-league-side-tottenham-hotspur-4466922|title=Leeds United transfer latest: Whites exercise recall option to allow Djed Spence to return to Premier League side Tottenham Hotspur|date=4 January 2024|access-date=6 October 2024|website=Yorkshire Post}}</ref>

On 4 January 2024, Leeds triggered a break clause to terminate Spence's loan spell, seeing him return to Tottenham Hotspur.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 January 2024 |title=Djed Spence returns to Tottenham Hotspur |url=https://www.leedsunited.com/en/news/djed-spence-returns-to-tottenham-hotspur |access-date=4 January 2024 |website=www.leedsunited.com |language=en}}</ref> Leeds manager [[Daniel Farke]] said the decision was made due to concerns about Spence's attitude.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Young |first=Alex |date=2024-01-05 |title=Why Leeds sent Spence back to Tottenham amid attitude concerns |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/tottenham-djed-spence-leeds-loan-transfer-news-latest-b1130614.html |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=The Standard |language=en}}</ref>

====Loan to Genoa====
On 11 January 2024, Spence signed for [[Serie A]] club [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]] on a loan deal until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 January 2024 |title=Djes Spence nuovo giocatore del Genoa |trans-title=Djed Spence is a new Genoa player |url=https://genoacfc.it/2024/01/11/djed-spence-e-un-nuovo-giocatore-del-genoa/ |access-date=11 January 2024 |publisher=Genoa CFC |language=it}}</ref> He made 16 Serie A appearances for the ''Rossoblù'' in the second half of [[2023–24 Genoa CFC season|the season]]. However, the club was unable to meet the option to buy fee of £8.5m at the end of his loan spell and he returned to Tottenham Hotspur.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cg3j6xqqq8qo|title=Genoa fail to agree cut-price deal for Spence|date=3 July 2024|access-date=6 October 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

====Return to Tottenham Hotspur====
Ahead of the 2024–25 season, Spence was omitted from Tottenham's [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] squad. He was, however, registered for domestic competitions.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mashiter |first=Nick |date=2025-05-19 |title=Djed Spence: 'Relaxed' star's journey from Spurs outcast to key man |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cly85plk074o |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 19 August 2024, Spence made his first appearance for Tottenham since January 2023 in their opening fixture of the [[2024–25 Tottenham Hotspur F.C. season|2024–25 season]], replacing [[Pedro Porro]] as a substitute in a 1–1 draw with [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] in the [[2024–25 Premier League|Premier League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/english-premier-league-live-updates-tottenham-hotspur-v-leicester-city-20240819-p5k3mw.html|title=English Premier League live updates: Tottenham Hotspur v Leicester City|date=19 August 2024|access-date=6 October 2024|website=The Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref> He scored his first competitive goal for the club in a 2–1 [[2024–25 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] win over [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] on 17 September.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-18 |title=Coventry 1–2 Tottenham: Win papers over performance |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c749x977veko |access-date=2024-09-19 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> His first start for Tottenham came on 15 December 2024 (881 days after signing for the club) in a 5–0 win against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Harris |first=Jay |date=2024-12-22 |title=It took Djed Spence 881 days to make his first start for Tottenham. It was worth the wait |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5996822/2024/12/16/djed-spence-tottenham-hotspur-first-start/ |access-date=2025-08-29 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

Following long-term injuries to defenders [[Micky van de Ven]], [[Cristian Romero (Argentine footballer)|Cristian Romero]], and [[Destiny Udogie]], Djed Spence received an extended run in the Tottenham Hotspur starting lineup from December 2024 to February 2025.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Harris |first=Jay |title=It took Djed Spence 881 days to make his first start for Tottenham. It was worth the wait |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5996822/2024/12/16/djed-spence-tottenham-hotspur-first-start/ |access-date=2025-02-17 |work=The New York Times |date=22 December 2024 |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Spence was named Player of the Match for his performance in Tottenham's 1–0 win over Manchester United on 16 February 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brown |first=Jamie |date=2025-02-16 |title=Djed Spence just proved a clear point to Ange Postecoglou vs Man United with Tottenham boss facing big dilemma |url=https://tbrfootball.com/djed-spence-just-proved-a-clear-point-to-ange-postecoglou-vs-man-united-with-tottenham-boss-facing-big-dilemma/#:~:text=Djed%20Spence%20claimed%20his%20second,sheet%20at%20Tottenham%20Hotspur%20Stadium. |access-date=2025-02-17 |website=TBR Football |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 22 February 2025, Spence scored his first Premier League goal in a 4–1 win over [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Edwards |first=Andy |title=Ipswich 1–4 Tottenham Hotspur: Spurs survive early, thrive late |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/soccer/news/how-to-watch-ipswich-vs-tottenham-hotspur-live-stream-link-tv-channel-team-news-prediction |access-date=2025-02-23 |work=NBC Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> He was selected in the squad that played the [[2025 UEFA Europa League final]], entering the game as a substitute, and helping Tottenham to win their first trophy for seventeen years.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Stone |first1=Simon |title=UEFA Europa League Final: Tottenham 1–0 Manchester United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cz9yney9391t |website=BBC Sport |access-date=30 August 2025 |date=21 May 2025}}</ref>

On 18 August 2025, Tottenham announced that Spence had signed a new long-term contract with the club.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Djed Spence signs new deal |url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2025/august/djed-spence-signs-new-deal/ |access-date=2025-08-18 |website=Tottenham Hotspur |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
In March 2022, Spence earned a first international call up to the [[England national under-21 football team|England Under-21 squad]] for the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|European Championship Qualifying matches]] against [[Andorra national under-21 football team|Andorra]] and [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2022/Mar/18/england-mu21s-squad-named-for-andorra-and-albania-games-20221803|title=Elliott, Jones and Lamptey among England MU21 recalls|publisher=Football Association|date=18 March 2022|work=England Football|accessdate=20 March 2022|first=Frank|last=Smith}}</ref> He made his debut as a substitute during a 3–0 victory away to the latter on 29 March 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.englandfootball.com/articles/2022/Mar/29/albania-england-mu21s-euro-qualifier-match-live-report-20222803|title=Report: Albania 0–3 England MU21s |work=England Football|date=29 March 2022|publisher=Football Association|access-date=30 March 2022|first=Tom|last=Masters}}</ref>

Spence was called up to the senior [[England national football team|England]] squad for the first time on 29 August 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |title=England squad LIVE: Trent Alexander-Arnold dropped by Thomas Tuchel |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/ce93pj8zpn4t |access-date=2025-08-29 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He became the first Muslim player to receive a call up to the senior men's team.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mallows |first=Tom |date=4 September 2025 |title=Spence hopes to inspire as first Muslim England player |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cn95ldwqwygo }}</ref> On 9 September 2025, Spence made his debut for the English senior squad in a 5–0 victory against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group K|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]], replacing [[Reece James]] in the 69th minute.<ref>{{cite web |date=9 September 2025 |title=Serbia 0–5 England |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cpd9ld1g1vwt |website= |location= |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |access-date=9 September 2025}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Spence primarily plays as a right-back, and is known for his pace and dribbling ability.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Carey |first=Liam Tharme and Mark |title=What Tottenham can expect from Djed Spence: Crosses, beating a man, but lots to learn |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3426306/2022/07/19/djed-spence-tottenham-forest/ |access-date=2022-09-01 |website=The Athletic |date=19 July 2022 |language=en}}</ref> He has been praised by [[Ian Wright]], who described him as "combative, technical, swashbuckling", and [[Wes Morgan]], who compared him to a Rolls-Royce.<ref>{{Cite web |last=McGovern |first=Ste |date=2022-01-14 |title=Ian Wright pays Djed Spence huge compliment after Arsenal display |url=https://www.nottinghampost.com/sport/football/football-news/ian-wright-djed-spence-arsenal-6495826 |access-date=2022-09-01 |website=NottinghamshireLive |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Johns |first=Craig |date=2022-02-07 |title=Scouting mission, pundit praise & ex-boss valuation – Spence impresses |url=https://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/spence-forest-middlesbrough-tottenham-praise-23008716 |access-date=2022-09-01 |website=TeessideLive |language=en}}</ref>

